# 🔥 PFIS — Revised Plan (Post Architect Review)

> This document incorporates all feedback from the senior-architect review into a battle-tested execution plan.

---

## 1. Revised Verdict: 80–85% → Targeting 95%+

### What Was Strong (Kept As-Is)
- ✅ Product positioning ("intelligence system" not "tracker")
- ✅ 9-layer separation of concerns
- ✅ Raw email retention for re-processing
- ✅ Confidence scoring on transactions
- ✅ Merchant normalization layer
- ✅ Pipeline design (matches real fintech patterns)

### 7 Critical Fixes Applied

| # | Problem | Fix Applied |
|---|---------|-------------|
| 1 | Regex overconfidence | Multi-tier parsing: Rules → Heuristics → AI fallback |
| 2 | No parser versioning | `parser_version` column + re-parse capability |
| 3 | No feedback loop | User correction layer → feeds back into rules |
| 4 | Dedup fragility | Multi-level dedup strategy (strong/medium/weak) |
| 5 | No sync tracking | `sync_runs` table added |
| 6 | No error recovery | Dead Letter Queue (DLQ) for failed parses |
| 7 | Insights too basic | Trend comparison + anomaly detection added |

---

## 2. Revised Data Model

### New Tables Added

```sql
-- Parser versioning on transactions
ALTER TABLE transactions ADD COLUMN parser_version INTEGER DEFAULT 1;

-- Sync tracking
CREATE TABLE sync_runs (
    id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID REFERENCES users(id),
    start_time TIMESTAMP,
    end_time TIMESTAMP,
    emails_fetched INTEGER,
    emails_processed INTEGER,
    emails_failed INTEGER,
    errors JSONB,
    status VARCHAR(20) -- 'running', 'completed', 'failed'
);

-- User corrections (feedback loop)
CREATE TABLE user_corrections (
    id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    transaction_id UUID REFERENCES transactions(id),
    field_corrected VARCHAR(50), -- 'merchant', 'category', 'amount'
    old_value TEXT,
    new_value TEXT,
    corrected_at TIMESTAMP
);

-- Dead Letter Queue
CREATE TABLE parse_failures (
    id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    email_id UUID REFERENCES raw_emails(id),
    error_message TEXT,
    parser_version INTEGER,
    retry_count INTEGER DEFAULT 0,
    last_retry_at TIMESTAMP,
    resolved BOOLEAN DEFAULT FALSE
);

-- Transaction fingerprint for dedup
ALTER TABLE transactions ADD COLUMN fingerprint VARCHAR(64) UNIQUE;
```

### Complete Entity Diagram (Revised)

```mermaid
erDiagram
    USERS ||--o{ GMAIL_ACCOUNTS : has
    USERS ||--o{ RAW_EMAILS : receives
    USERS ||--o{ TRANSACTIONS : owns
    USERS ||--o{ BUDGETS : sets
    USERS ||--o{ SYNC_RUNS : triggers
    RAW_EMAILS ||--o| TRANSACTIONS : generates
    RAW_EMAILS ||--o| PARSE_FAILURES : fails_to
    TRANSACTIONS ||--o{ USER_CORRECTIONS : corrected_by
    TRANSACTIONS }o--|| CATEGORIES : belongs_to
    TRANSACTIONS }o--|| MERCHANTS : references
```

