## 10. Success Metrics (DEFINED)

| Metric | Target | How to Measure |
|--------|--------|---------------|
| Parsing accuracy | ≥ 80% | Correct extractions / total emails |
| Duplicate rate | ≤ 2% | Duplicate txns / total txns |
| Processing speed | < 2 sec/email | Timer on parse pipeline |
| Dashboard refresh | < 10 sec after sync | End-to-end timing |
| User corrections | Decreasing over time | Corrections per week |

---

## 11. Test Dataset Requirement (CRITICAL)

### Before writing ANY parser code:

Create **30–50 sample emails** covering:

| Bank | Count | Formats |
|------|-------|---------|
| HDFC | 10 | Debit, Credit, UPI, Card |
| SBI | 8 | Debit, Credit, NEFT |
| ICICI | 8 | Debit, Credit, UPI |
| UPI Apps | 8 | GPay, PhonePe, Paytm |
| Edge Cases | 6 | Missing merchant, no ref_id, HTML emails |

Each sample has **expected output** → this is your ground truth for testing.

---

## 12. Execution Strategy: Vertical Slices

### ❌ Wrong: Horizontal (Build All Backend → All Parser → All UI)
### ✅ Right: Vertical (Each iteration = end-to-end working flow)

```mermaid
gantt
    title Vertical Slice Execution
    dateFormat  YYYY-MM-DD
    section Phase 0
    Setup & Foundation           :p0, 2026-05-05, 3d
    section Phase 1
    Gmail Integration            :p1, after p0, 4d
    section Phase 2
    Parsing Engine               :p2, after p1, 7d
    section Phase 3
    Processing Layer             :p3, after p2, 5d
    section Phase 4
    Dashboard                    :p4, after p3, 5d
    section Phase 5
    Insights (MVP+)              :p5, after p4, 3d
```

### Phase 0: Setup (2–3 days)
- [x] Repo setup
- [x] PostgreSQL + schema
- [x] Backend skeleton (FastAPI)
- [x] Can insert/fetch dummy transactions
- **Exit criteria:** Dummy transaction visible via API

### Phase 1: Gmail (3–4 days)
- [ ] OAuth flow
- [ ] Fetch last 20 emails
- [ ] Store raw emails
- [ ] No duplicates on re-fetch
- **Exit criteria:** Raw emails visible in DB

### Phase 2: Parsing (5–7 days) — **60% effort here**
- [ ] Test dataset created (30+ emails)
- [ ] HDFC parser working
- [ ] Amount extraction ≥ 90%
- [ ] Merchant extraction ≥ 70%
- [ ] Confidence scoring
- [ ] Parser versioning
- **Exit criteria:** 60–70% correct parsing on test dataset

### Phase 3: Processing (4–5 days)
- [ ] Dedup engine (multi-level)
- [ ] Merchant normalization
- [ ] Category mapping (rule-based)
- [ ] DLQ for failed parses
- **Exit criteria:** Clean transaction table, no duplicates

### Phase 4: Dashboard (4–5 days)
- [ ] Transaction list
- [ ] Monthly total
- [ ] Category chart
- [ ] Confidence indicators in UI
- [ ] User correction buttons
- **Exit criteria:** User can "see" their money

### Phase 5: Insights (3 days, optional MVP+)
- [ ] Top merchants
- [ ] Category percentages
- [ ] Month-over-month trend
- **Exit criteria:** At least 3 auto-generated insights

---

## 13. Iteration Cycle (Per Feature)

```
Plan → Build → Test → Measure → Fix → Repeat
```

**Example — Parsing Feature:**
1. **Iteration 1:** Parse amount only → measure accuracy
2. **Iteration 2:** Add merchant extraction → measure
3. **Iteration 3:** Add date extraction → measure
4. **Iteration 4:** Edge cases + improve → measure

> [!CAUTION]
> **Don't try to build perfect parser in one go.** Iterate.

---

## 14. Testing Strategy

| Type | What | When |
|------|------|------|
| **Unit** | Each parser: input email → expected output | Every parser change |
| **Integration** | Email → Parsed → Stored → API returns it | Each phase |
| **Regression** | Old emails still parse correctly after parser update | Before deploy |
| **Edge Case** | Missing merchant, no amount, HTML emails | Phase 2 |

---

## 15. Engineering Discipline

### Logging (Non-Negotiable)
```
✅ Email received: {sender, subject, id}
✅ Parse result: {success/fail, confidence, fields_extracted}
✅ Dedup result: {new/duplicate/flagged}
✅ Sync run: {fetched, processed, failed}
```

### Observability Dashboard
- Emails processed today
- Parse success rate
- Average confidence score
- Failed parses count
- User corrections count

### Common Mistakes to Avoid

| Mistake | Why It's Bad |
|---------|-------------|
| Overbuilding AI early | You don't have enough data yet |
| Ignoring data quality | Garbage in → garbage out |
| No logging | Can't debug production issues |
| No test dataset | You'll keep guessing |
| Building UI first | Biggest trap — backend is the core |

---

## 16. MVP Definition (Testable Outcome)

> **"User connects Gmail → system shows at least 10 correct transactions → dashboard updates automatically"**

That's the testable MVP. Not a feature list — an outcome.

---

## 17. Architecture Diagram (Final Revised)

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    GMAIL["Gmail API<br/>(historyId sync)"] --> QUEUE["Message Queue<br/>(BullMQ/Celery)"]
    QUEUE --> WORKER["Background Worker"]
    WORKER --> FILTER["Filter Engine<br/>(Transaction vs OTP vs Promo)"]
    FILTER --> REGISTRY["Parser Registry"]
    REGISTRY --> HDFC["HDFC Parser"]
    REGISTRY --> SBI["SBI Parser"]
    REGISTRY --> GENERIC["Generic Parser"]
    REGISTRY -->|"conf < 0.5"| LLM["AI Fallback"]
    
    HDFC --> DEDUP["Multi-Level Dedup"]
    SBI --> DEDUP
    GENERIC --> DEDUP
    LLM --> DEDUP
    
    DEDUP --> NORM["Merchant Normalizer"]
    NORM --> CAT["Categorizer"]
    CAT --> DB["PostgreSQL"]
    
    WORKER -->|"Parse Fail"| DLQ["Dead Letter Queue"]
    DLQ -->|"Retry 3x"| WORKER
    DLQ -->|"Final Fail"| REVIEW["Manual Review"]
    
    DB --> INSIGHTS["Insights Engine"]
    INSIGHTS --> API["REST API"]
    API --> DASH["Dashboard"]
    DASH -->|"Corrections"| FEEDBACK["Feedback Loop"]
    FEEDBACK --> REGISTRY
    FEEDBACK --> NORM
    
    SYNC["Sync Tracker"] --> DB
    WORKER --> SYNC
```

---

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **The single most important takeaway:**  
> *"Don't try to build a complete system. Build a working pipeline first."*  
> Email → Parse → Store → Display. Get this loop working end-to-end, then iterate.

